  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Patient Service Associate (Office Hours)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company’s Profile:</strong></p><p>Our client is a leading public healthcare institution that provides seamless, team-based care across all stages of a patient’s health journey. Serving a diverse community, they are committed to innovation, collaboration, and using technology to deliver person-centered, holistic care. Awarded as one of the Best Employers in 2025, they are looking for qualified individuals to join their dynamic environment dedicated to improving lives within the community.<br /></p><p><br />Work Location: West side polyclinics</p><p></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Conduct financial advice to patient/NOK on the estimated hospital bills, available subsidies and schemes and various modes of payment.</li><li>Refer appropriate cases to Business Office/Medical Social Worker for financial assistance schemes that patient may be eligible for.</li><li>Ensure proper documentation and follow up is done for all inflight cases until patient discharge.</li><li>Assist patients in their billing enquiries.</li><li>Collect deposits and any outstanding bills for eligible patients.</li><li>Collect payment for other items ordered/applied by medical team such as rehabilitation items, mobility aids etc.</li><li>Explain and advise patient on the various forms and the necessary proof of documentation needed.</li><li>Ensure the original hardcopy of MCAF M/NEFR forms are submitted and send back to MOHH timely.</li><li>Ensure SAP system is updated whenever these forms are consented by patient.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>At least 1 year experience as Patient Service Associate, experience in any clinic/hospital setting will be a strong advantage</li><li>Strong communication skills, passionate to interact with patients</li><li>Minimum O levels education qualification</li></ul><p><br />Interested candidates may <strong>whatsapp your resume to 8977 7062</strong>. Only shortlisted applicants will be contacted.<br /><br />By submitting your personal data and/or resume, you give consent to the collection, use and disclosure of your personal data and/or resume by the company (or its agent) for the purpose of the processing and administration by company relating to this job application.</p><p>Cassie Chan | R2197426</p><p>EnviroDynamics Solutions Pte Ltd | EA No: 12C6285</p>",
